column5: Video colour primaries indicating the chromaticity coordinates of the source colour primaries.
Video colour transfer characteristics indicating the opto-electronic transfer characteristic of the source picture.
Video matrix colour coefficients describing the matrix coefficients used in deriving luma and chroma signals from the green, blue, and red primaries.
Video Full Range specifying the scaling and offset values applied in association with the Video matrix colour coefficients.
Video frame packing indicating the type of packing arrangement used in video frames
Quincunx Sampling Flag indicatomh whether a quincunx sampling structure is used in the frame packed video representation.
Interpretation of packed video frames indicating the intended interpretation of the constituent frames.

For Adaptation Sets or Representations that contain a video component that conforms to ISO/IEC 14496-10, this URI is defined. The @value is the value as defined for VideoFramePackingType in ISO/IEC 23001-8 [4].

For Adaptation Sets or Representations that contain a video component that conforms to ISO/IEC 13818-1, this URI is defined. The @value is the value as defined for VideoFramePackingType in ISO/IEC 23001-8 [4].
